fields.description:
In Studio, our JIRA logs are being filled with messages like:

{noformat}
2008-04-09 18:48:40.198947500 2008-04-09 18:48:40,104 TP-Processor19 ERROR [crowd.integration.osuser.CrowdCredentialsProvider] Failed to find user:
2008-04-09 18:48:40.198950500 2008-04-09 18:48:40,105 TP-Processor19 WARN [atlassian.seraph.filter.TrustedApplicationsFilter] User '' referenced by trusted application: '7F00000101185CF40002594001C20C74' is not found.
{noformat}

In crowd-atlassian-user/src/main/java/com/atlassian/crowd/integration/osuser/CrowdBaseProvider.java, we have the code:

{code}
    protected SOAPPrincipal findPrincipalByName(String username)
        ....
        if (principal == null)
        {
        ....
          catch (ObjectNotFoundException oe)
            {
                logger.error("Failed to find user: " + username);
            }
{code}

This is presumably a Studio bug, as our code shouldn't be looking up user ''.
